0to%20do%20in%20his%20retirement.%20Mueller%2C%20who%20drives%20in%20Naples%2C%20Florida%2C%20only%20works%20one%20day%20a%20week%20since%20he%20doesn't%20rely%20on%20driving%20to%20stay%20afloat%2C%20and%20he%20uses%20his%20earnings%20for%20expenses%20like%20dinners%20or%20filling%20up%20his%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20driving%20is%20beneficial%20to%20do%20besides%20the%20financial%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20it%20gives%20them%20something%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Mueller%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20that%20they're%20still%20a%20part%20of%20their%20community%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20them%20physically%20active.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20like%20Bob%20Milosavljevi%C4%87%2C%2072%2C%20rely%20on%20driving%20income%20to%20supplement%20his%20Social%20Security%20income.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmassachusetts-uber-lyft-driving-minimum-wage-gig-work-lobbying-competition-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoston%3C%2Fa%3E%20driver%20worked%20as%20an%20IT%20and%20cybersecurity%20specialist%20and%20doesn't%20fully%20rely%20on%20driving%20income%20to%20get%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilosavljevi%C4%87%20said%20his%20main%20reason%20for%20starting%20ride-hail%20driving%20five%20years%20ago%20was%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20house%20and%20interact%20with%20people.%20Once%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20he%20said%20his%20personal%20finances%20weren't%20great%2C%20and%20the%20extra%20income%20helped%20with%20rising%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20options%20for%20people%20like%20me%20short%20of%20going%20out%20and%20finding%20a%20real%20job%20like%20a%20desk%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20worked%20my%20whole%20life%20to%20get%20away%20from%20that%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20looking%20forward%20to%20having%20to%20go%20back%20to%20that.%20I%20will%20avoid%20it%20at%20all%20costs.%20But%20I%20see%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20any%20easier%20for%20us%20than%20it%20is%20today