ho%20worked%20for%20three%20years%20as%20a%20member%20of%20technical%20staff%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjan-leike-ilya-sutskever-resignations-superalignment-openai-superintelligence-safe-humanity-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20superalignment%20team.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20speaking%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DdzQlRt3y5mU%26ab_channel%3DAlexKantrowitz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eepisode%20of%20tech%20YouTuber%20Alex%20Kantrowitz's%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20on%20July%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20my%20three%20years%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20I%20would%20sometimes%20ask%20myself%20a%20question.%20Was%20the%20path%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20on%20more%20like%20the%20Apollo%20program%20or%20more%20like%20the%20Titanic%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20engineer's%20concerns%20stem%20largely%20from%20OpenAI's%20plan%20to%20achieve%20Artificial%20General%20Intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20the%20point%20where%20AI%20can%20teach%20itself%20%E2%80%94%20while%20also%20debuting%20paid%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20on%20this%20trajectory%20to%20change%20the%20world%2C%20and%20yet%20when%20they%20release%20things%2C%20their%20priorities%20are%20more%20like%20a%20product%20company.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20is%20what%20is%20most%20unsettling%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225a42c19-2982-4517-addf-6a1881609025%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EApollo%20vs%20Titanic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Saunders%20spent%20more%20time%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20he%20felt%20leaders%20were%20making%20decisions%20more%20akin%20to%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20the%20Titanic%2C%20prioritizing%20getting%20out%20newer%2C%20shinier%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20would%20have%20much%20preferred%20a%20mood%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fevery-nasa-apollo-mission-in-history-explained-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApollo%20space%20program's%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20he%20characterized%20as%20an%20example%20of%20an%20ambitious%20project%20that%20%26quot%3Bwas%20about%20carefully%20predicting%20and%20assessing%20risks%26quot%3B%20while%20pushing%20scientific%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20when%20big%20problems%20happened%2C%20like%20Apollo%2013%2C%20they%20had%20enough%20sort%20of%20like%20redundancy%2C%20and%20were%20able%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20everyone%20back%20safely%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Titanic%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20built%20by%20White%20Star%20Line%20as%20it%20competed%20with%20its%20rivals%20to%20make%20bigger%20cruise%20liners%2C%20Saunders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaunders%20fears%20that%2C%20like%20with%20the%20Titanic's%20safeguards%2C%20OpenAI%20could%20be%20relying%20too%20heavily%20on%20its%20current%20measures%20and%20research%20for%20AI%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLots%20of%20work%20went%20into%20making%20the%20ship%20safe%20and%20building%20watertight%20compartments%20so%20that%20they%20could%20say%20that%20it%20was%20unsinkable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there%20weren't%20enough%20lifeboats%20for%20everyone.%20So%20when%20disaster%20struck%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20died.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20the%20Apollo%20missions%20were%20conducted%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20a%20Cold%20War%20space%20race%20with%20Russia.%20They%20also%20involved%20several%20serious%20casualties%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fhistory%2F55-years-ago-the-apollo-1-fire-and-its-aftermath%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3D28%252C%25201967%252C%2520the%2520day%2520after%2CChaffee.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20NASA%20astronauts%20who%20died%20in%201967%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20an%20electrical%20fire%20during%20a%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExplaining%20his%20analogy%20further%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Saunders%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20the%20Apollo%20program%20had%20its%20own%20tragedies.%20It%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20develop%20AGI%20or%20any%20new%20technology%20with%20zero%20risk.%20What%20I%20would%20like%20to%20see%20is%20the%20company%20taking%20all%20possible%20reasonable%20steps%20to%20prevent%20these%20risks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f86480a-e53d-47cc-ac54-2cd5458d821d%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20needs%20more%20'lifeboats%2C'%20Saunders%20says%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESaunders%20told%20BI%20that%20a%20%26quot%3BTitanic%20disaster%26quot%3B%20for%20AI%20could%20manifest%20in%20a%20model%20that%20can%20launch%20a%20large-scale%20cyberattack%2C%20persuade%20people%20en%20masse%20in%20a%20campaign%2C%20or%20help%20build%20biological%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20near%20term%2C%20OpenAI%20should%20invest%20in%20additional%20%26quot%3Blifeboats%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20delaying%20the%20release%20of%20new%20language%20models%20so%20teams%20can%20research%20potential%20harms%2C%20he%20said%20in%20his%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20the%20superalignment%20team%2C%20Saunders%20led%20a%20group%20of%20four%20staff%20dedicated%20to%20understanding%20how%20AI%20language%20models%20behave%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20said%20humans%20don't%20know%20enough%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20in%20the%20future%20we%20build%20AI%20systems%20as%20smart%20or%20smarter%20than%20most%20humans%2C%20we%20will%20need%20techniques%20to%20be%20able%20to%20tell%20if%20these%20systems%20are%20hiding%20capabilities%20or%20motivations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ilya%20Sutskever%2C%20Russian%20Israeli-Canadian%20computer%20scientist%20and%20co-founder%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20speaks%20at%20a%20conference%20in%20Tel%20Aviv.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%